crowdsourced_yara_results.description: This signature fires on the presence of Base64 encoded URI prefixes (http:// and https://) across any file. The simple presence of such strings is not inherently an indicator of malicious content, but is worth further investigation.

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis:
This code functions as a remote orchestrator for command execution on a target Windows machine. It contains a base64-encoded portable executable, which is deployed as a temporary service. The orchestrator uses SMB protocol to connect to the target, authenticate, and install the embedded service.

The installed service establishes named pipes for communication. The orchestrator then uses these pipes to send an initialization packet containing the command to execute and its arguments, along with flags to specify execution context (e.g., SYSTEM privileges or user impersonation). It also sets up interactive standard input, standard output, and standard error channels via additional named pipes. This allows for real-time sending of commands and receiving of their output. After command execution, the orchestrator attempts to uninstall the deployed service.
